[[File:Bhummaso.jpg|thumb|An artistic rendition of an ''Bhummaso'']]
'''Bhummaso''' ({{lang-my|ဘုမ္မစိုး}}; also called as '''Myay Saung Nat''' ({{lang-my|မြေစောင့်နတ်}}; lit. "Earth Guardian Spirit"), are Burmese ''[[nat (spirit)|nats]]'' (spirits) who inhabit the roots of trees and serve as guardians of the earth. ''Bhummaso'' is derived from [[Pali]] ''buma deva'' ({{my|ဘုမ္မဒေဝ}}), which literally means "deity of the earth."{{sfn|MLC|1993}}

They are related to ''[[Yokkaso]]'' ({{my|ရုက္ခစိုး}}) and ''[[Akathaso]]'' ({{my|အာကာသစိုး}}), who respectively live on the tree trunks and sky. ''Akathaso'' are guardian spirits of the sky while ''[[Yokkaso]]'' are guardian spirits of tree.{{sfn|MLC|1993}}<ref name="nats">{{cite web|url=http://www.green-lotus.org/2014/06/ |title=Buddhism and animism in Myanmar |publisher=Green Lotus |date= |accessdate=}}</ref>

