'''Edward Klinik''' (July 21, 1919 – August 24, 1942) was a [[Poles|Polish]] and [[Roman Catholic]] anti-Nazi resistance fighter. He was guillotined in a prison in [[Dresden]]. He is one of the [[108 Martyrs of World War II]] who were [[Beatification|beatified]] by Pope [[John Paul II]] in 1999.

