{{Infobox tractor |name = Kunduz |image = |caption = |national origin= [[Turkey]] |manufacturer = [[FNSS Defence Systems]], [[Turkey]] |production = 2013-present |length = |width = |height = |weight = |propulsion = Tracks |type = Amphibious armoured bulldozer }}
'''Kunduz''' or '''AZMİM''' (short for '''A'''mfibik '''Z'''ırhlı '''M'''uharebe '''İ'''stihkam İş '''M'''akinesi), is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] [[continuous track|tracked]] [[amphibious vehicle|amphibious]] [[military engineering vehicle|combat engineering]] [[armoured bulldozer]].<ref>http://www.fnss.com.tr/urun/kunduz</ref>
Unique of its art in the world, the heavy equipment was developed and produced in less than four-years work for the [[Turkish Armed Forces]] (TSK) by the Turkish company [[FNSS Defence Systems]]. The prototype was delivered to the TSK on January 11, 2013 in [[Ankara]]. AZMİM will be operated to move earth, clear terrain obstacles, cut steep slopes and stabilize stream banks for easy river crossing of combat vehicles during [[Turkish Army]]'s [[amphibious warfare]].<ref name="h">{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/ekonomi/22339848.asp |newspaper=[[Hürriyet]] Ekonomi |title=Türk ordusuna yüzer dozer geliyor |date=2013-01-11 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2013-01-13 }}</ref>
The contract to develop the armoured amphibious bulldozer was signed on March 10, 2009 between the [[Ministry of National Defence (Turkey)|Ministry of National Defence]] and the FNSS. The project, which began to develop on June 15, 2009, foresees the production of twelve units until the end of 2013.<ref name="h"/> The first was delivered on January 11, 2013.<ref>[http://www.armyrecognition.com/january_2013_army_military_defense_industry_news/fnss_has_delivered_the_azmim_aace_amphibious_armoured_earthmover_to_turksih_army_1401133.html AZMIM AACE Amphibious Armoured Earthmover delivered to Turkish Army] - Armyrecognition.com, January 14, 2013</ref>
==Specifications== AZMİM has two crew, one operator and one attendant. It is capable of shoveling, smoothing, hauling and excavating. Tests showed that it is resistant to [[land mine]]s and [[armour-piercing shot and shell]]. AZMİM is equipped with daylight camera system, [[night vision device]], multi-purpose [[LED display]] and air conditioner. The tracked vehicle can accompany other military combat vehicles without the need of a carrier thanks to its max. speed of {{convert|45|km/h|mph|abbr=on}}. Two installed [[pump-jet]]s enable the amphibious bulldozer to conduct a 360 degrees turning movement in rip current waters.<ref name="h"/>
