The '''Indian Ocean Naval Symposium''', commonly known as '''IONS''', are a series of biennial meetings among the [[littoral]] states of the [[Indian Ocean|Indian Ocean region]]. It provides a forum to increase maritime security cooperation, providing a forum for discussion of regional maritime issues and promote friendly relationships among the member nations.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ions.global/|title=Welcome to Indian Ocean Naval Symposium {{!}} Indian Ocean Naval Symposium|website=www.ions.global|access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://ions.gov.in/about_ions|title=About IONS {{!}} Indian Ocean Naval Symposium|website=ions.gov.in|language=en|access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=http://www.navy.gov.au/ions|title=Indian Ocean Naval Symposium|last=Navy|first=corporateName=Royal Australian|website=www.navy.gov.au|access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i0YKDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT154&lpg=PT154&dq=maldives+IONS&source=bl&ots=DGwrv3XyGi&sig=3mSadm3PWNqYll53YR6_JMpZVXw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjs4puZmeDXAhWChlQKHdWZA9AQ6AEIRDAF#v=onepage&q=maldives%20IONS&f=false|title=The Indo Pacific Region: Security Dynamics and Challenges|last=Tewari|first=Sharad|last2=Khanijo|first2=Dr Roshan|date=2016-10-10|publisher=Vij Books India Pvt Ltd|isbn=9789385563300|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Joj7CwAAQBAJ&pg=PA32&dq=Indian+ocean+naval+symposium&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiT8bvEmeDXAhULsFQKHRHmCdEQ6AEILjAC#v=onepage&q=Indian%20ocean%20naval%20symposium&f=false|title=Indian Ocean Regionalism|last=Rumley|first=Dennis|last2=Doyle|first2=Timothy|date=2016-04-14|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781317585978|language=en}}</ref>
==History== The IONS a regional forum of Indian Ocean littoral states, represented by their Navy chiefs, was initiated and launched by [[India]] in February 2008<ref>http://defencereporter.com/navy/india-china-to-join-indian-ocean-exercise_92146.html</ref><ref>https://www.cna.org/cna_files/pdf/DRM-2016-U-013939-Final2.pdf</ref><ref>http://lkyspp2.nus.edu.sg/cag/publication/china-india-brief/china-india-brief-99</ref><ref>journals.christuniversity.in/index.php/artha/article/download/1569/1314</ref>
== Role == IONS is a security construct for the [[Indian Ocean|Indian Ocean region]] which is similar to the [[Western Pacific Naval Symposium]]. It is a voluntary initiative among the navies and maritime security agencies of the member nations. In addition to the symposiums, numerous other activities like workshops, essay competitions and lectures are also held under the umbrella of the organization.<ref name=":1" />
== Members and observers == The 35 member nations of the IONS are grouped into four sub-regions.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ions.global/ions-working-groups|title=IONS Working Groups {{!}} Indian Ocean Naval Symposium|website=www.ions.global|access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite web|url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/foreign-affairs/2017/11/27/president-inaugurates-naval-exercise/|title=President inaugurates 32-nation naval exercise {{!}} Dhaka Tribune|website=www.dhakatribune.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref>
