[[File:Polizia san marino posto di blocco.jpg|thumbnail|300px|Fortress Guard and Civil Police [[border checkpoint]].]]
'''Law enforcement in [[San Marino]]''' is the responsibility of the centralized [[Civil Police (San Marino)|Civil Police]],<ref name="Government home page">[http://www.sanmarinosite.com/eng/corpimilitari.html Government home page]</ref> together with the [[Corps of Gendarmerie of San Marino]] (militarized police), and the [[Military of San Marino#The Guard of the Rock (or Fortress Guard Corps)|Fortress Guard]] (border patrol with military status),<ref>The three organizations are listed as Policing agencies on the [http://www.esteri.sm/on-line/en/Home/Link/PoliceDepartment.html website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs]</ref> have been providing law enforcement in San Marino since a statute in 1987, which redefined their roles,<ref>[http://www-rohan.sdsu.edu/faculty/rwinslow/europe/sanmarino.html Crime and Society: A Comparative Criminology Tour of the World] Retrieved 15 May 2007</ref> further supported by revised regulations for both the Gendarmerie and the Fortress Guard, which was approved by the [[Government of San Marino]] in 2008.<ref>Referenced [http://www.esteri.sm/on-line/en/Home/News/articolo1000118.html here].</ref> Under the 2008 regulations the Gendarmerie and the Fortress Guards are responsible for [[policing]], [[criminal investigation]], [[prison|national penitentiary]], [[Guard Mounting|changing the guard]], [[Border guard|border patrol]], [[Custom controls|customs control]], [[Body guard|personal protection]], and [[national security]], while the Civil Police are tasked with [[tax collection]], [[Security|domestic security]], [[Road traffic control|traffic control]], and [[civil defence]].<ref name="Government home page"/><ref>Re-referenced here [[:it:Polizia Civile (San Marino)]]</ref> All three agencies are subordinate to the Secretary of State of Home Affairs.<ref>Government of San Marino [http://www.sanmarinosite.com/eng/corpimilitari.html] Retrieved 3 May 2012</ref> San Marino is also part of the international policing organization [[Interpol]], and as such there is an Interpol office in [[City of San Marino|San Marino City]].<ref>Full details [http://www.esteri.sm/on-line/en/Home/Link/Interpol.html here].</ref>

At the end of 2012, there were 160 police officers serving in San Marino; this includes: 70 Gendarmerie,<ref>[http://www.interphonef4.com/filemanager/cms_cellularline/img_interphone/video_immagini/immagini/gendarmeria_590x400.jpg Yearly Gendarmerie Photo]</ref> 50 Civil Police,<ref>[http://www.worldstatesmen.org/San_Marino.html Public Security Forces > Civil Police<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and 40 Fortress Guard.<ref>[http://www.mhsa.org.au/documents/act/LeGrognard2011-07.pdf Military units of San Marino > Fortress Guard]</ref> While total law enforcement expenditures amounted to [[$US|$]]13.3 million.<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?depth=1&hl=en&prev=/search%3Fq%3Dsegreteria%2Bdi%2Bstato%2Bper%2Ble%2Bfinanze%2Be%2Bbilancio%2B2012%26hl%3Den%26safe%3Doff%26biw%3D1366%26bih%3D704%26prmd%3Dimvns&rurl=translate.google.com&sl=it&twu=1&u=http://www.finanze.sm/contents/instance25/files/document/24042520PaginedaAll.MBil.pdf&usg=ALkJrhjrPXG2M834oFaQyn5lj7BQWHUlag 2012 Government Report<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

