The '''Nkoroo people''' are an [[Ijaw people|Ijaw]] people living in [[Nkoroo]], [[Rivers State]], [[Nigeria]], numbering about 4,700 (1989). The Nkoroo live in a close relationship with the [[Defaka people|Defaka]], with both groups living in the same town (Nkoro town). They speak their own language, called [[Nkoroo language|Nkoroo]].  The Nkoroo people refer to themselves and their language as 'Kirika', though 'Nkoroo' (or Nkọrọọ) is the standard name used by outsiders and in the scholarly literature.

